Hands down, Taste of Punjab is the BEST Indian Restaurant in Brooklyn AND Queens! I live in Brooklyn and I gladly trek all the way out to Richmond Hill ( the Van Wyck !!) , passing other Indian restaurants left and right, until I reach Taste of Punjab when I want Indian food. How did I find out about this restaurant? I googled "Best Chilly Mushroom in Queens" and Taste of Punjab was the top hit. Why settle for inferior quality?!? After reading all of the great reviews on the restaurant's website AND seamless, I decided to try them out. Of course the chilly mushrooms were amazing! The  vegetables ( I'm a vegan ) are always fresh, crisp, and deliciously seasoned. Naan and roti are always fresh and piping hot with that aroma that tempts you to eat it before you return back home! The staff is always friendly and inviting and will readily customize their dishes when you ask.  Trust me, all of the great reviews are authentic (including this one, ;-) )and not the work of a bot! However, let me warn you, once you eat here you won't be able to tolerate inferior quality anymore...and will find yourself compelled to travel to this restaurant !  Yes, if you want Indian food, Taste of Punjab is the ONLY Destination!
